story.storykicker: On the last day of withdrawal of nominations, the BJP withdrew 2 candidates paving way for unopposed elections.
story.storybody:
After creating a big hype, the elections for 10 Vidhan Parishad seats or the Upper House of Maharashtra Legislature finally went unopposed.

BJP WITHDREW 2 CANDIDATES

The elections had become crucial as BJP had fielded 6 candidates and supported one independent candidate making elections and Horse trading look inevitable. There was severe resentment within the BJP over giving tickets to outsiders and tainted leaders who had recently joined the party. A section of the BJP had openly criticised the party leadership for the 'wrong' choice. But finally on the last day of withdrawl of nominations, the BJP withdrew 2 candidates paving way for unopposed elections.

RANE MAKES A COMEBACK

The election also marks a big comeback for former Maharashtra CM and Congress leader Narayan Rane. The former Shiv Sainik had lost 2 back to back elections putting a big question mark on his political future. Rane's entry into the upper house is likely to make things difficult for the ruling alliance, especially the Shiv Sena as the aggressive leader is known for his knack of legislative procedures. Apart from Rane, Dhananjay Munde from the NCP has also been elected unopposed. With the BJP earlier deciding to field 7 candidates, Dhananjay would have been the one who may have felt the heat as the numbers were not in his party's favor. Dhananjay's re-entry would be a warning bell for his cousin and bete-noire Pankaja Munde.

MUMBAI CIVIC POLLS ON RADAR

The BJP also gave opportunity to its allies in this elections, as Sadabhau Khot of the Swabhimani Shetkari Sanghatana and Vinayak Mete of the Shivsangram got elected to the upper house. Former MNS leader Pravin Darekar who switched to the BJP recently, too will be in the upper house despite a section of party members strongly opposing his candidature following allegations of scam in the Mumbai district co-operative bank. RN Singh a former Congress leader too will be seen as a BJP legislator in the Vidhan Parishad. While giving opportunities to these leaders from Mumbai the BJP is seen strategising for the upcoming civic polls in Mumbai.
